    "text": "We claim conversely that if N has no 0's in its usual base 10 expansion, then this standard form is the unique base 10 over-expansion for N. This holds by induction on the number of digits of N: if 1 ≤ N≤9, then the result is clear. Otherwise, any base 10 overexpansion N= dk 10k+... + d/10 + do10° must have do = N (mod 10), which uniquely determines do since",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
